{"title_page": "Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye", "text_new": "{{redirect|Goodbye My Love, Goodbye|the 2006 Italian film|The Goodbye Kiss (film)}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Demis Roussos]]\n| album      = [[Forever and Ever (Demis Roussos album)|Forever and Ever]]\n| EP         =\n| written    =\n| published  = \n| released   = {{start date|1973}}\n| format     = 7\" vinyl single (45 RPM)\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n| length     =\n| label      = [[Philips Records|Philips]]\n| writer     = [[Leo Leandros]], [[Klaus Munro]]\n| composer   =\n| lyricist   =\n| producer   = [[Leo Leandros]]\n| prev_title = [[My Reason]]\n| prev_year  = 1972\n| title      =\n| next_title = [[Forever and Ever (Demis Roussos song)|Forever and Ever]]\" /<br />\"[[Velvet Mornings]]\n| next_year  = 1973\n| prev_track =\n| track_no   =\n| next_track =\n}}\n\n\"'''Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye'''\" is a song by Greek singer [[Demis Roussos]]. It was released as a [[single (music)|single]] in 1973.\n\nThe song was included on Roussos' 1973 album ''[[Forever and Ever (Demis Roussos album)|Forever and Ever]]''.\n\n== Background and writing ==\nThe song was written by [[Leo Leandros]] and [[Klaus Munro]]. The recording was produced by [[Leo Leandros]].<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" />\n\nThere is also a Spanish-language version, titled \"Adi\u00f3s, mi amor, adi\u00f3s\".<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.discogs.com/D%C3%A9mis-Roussos-Forever-And-Ever-Eternamente/release/4263690\n|title=D\u00e9mis Roussos* - Forever And Ever = Eternamente (Vinyl, LP, Album) at Discogs\n|accessdate=2017-10-26}}</ref>\n\n== Commercial performance ==\nThe song reached no. 1 in Germany, Switzerland,<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Demis+Roussos&titel=Goodbye%2C+My+Love%2C+Goodbye&cat=s\n|title=spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\n|accessdate=2017-10-23}}</ref> Belgium (Flanders),<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye (English)\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Demis+Roussos&titel=Goodbye%2C+My+Love%2C+Goodbye+%5BEnglish%5D&cat=s\n|title=spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye <nowiki>[English]</nowiki>\n|accessdate=2017-10-23}}</ref> and [[Spain]].\n\n== Track listings ==\n'''7\" single Philips 6009 318''' (1973, Germany, Ireland)<br />\n'''7\" single RTB S 53695''' (1973, Yugoslavia)\n: A. \"Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" (3:58)\n: B. \"Mara\" (3:59)<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" />\n\n'''7\" single Philips 6009 392''' (1973, Italy)\n: A. \"Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" (3:56)\n: B. \"My Friend The Wind\" (3:55)<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" /><ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye (English)\" />\n\n'''7\" single Philips 6009 364''' (1973, Netherlands)\n: A. \"Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" (3:58)\n: B. \"No Way Out\" (3:10)<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" /><ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye (English)\" />\n\n'''7\" single Philips 6009 381''' (1973, France, Portural<!--, Angola-->)\n: A. \"Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" (3:56)\n: B. \"Yellow Paper\" (3:04)<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" /><ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye (English)\" />\n\n'''7\" single Philips 60 09 400''' (1973, Spain)\n: A. \"Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" (3:56)\n: B. \"Lay It Down\" (3:45)<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye (English)\" />\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (1973)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|2|artist=Demis Roussos|song=Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 23, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Belgium (Flanders)|1|artist=Demis Roussos|song=Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 23, 2017}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| Germany<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" />\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|2|artist=Demis Roussos|song=Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 23, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Norway|3|artist=Demis Roussos|song=Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 23, 2017}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| Spain\n|align=\"center\"| 1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|1|artist=Demis Roussos|song=Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 23, 2017}}\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2015)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|98*|artist=Demis Roussos|song=Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 23, 2017}}\n|}\n:{{asterisk}} Charted posthumously in 2015\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of number-one singles of 1974 (Spain)]]\n* [[List of number-one singles from 1968 to 1979 (Switzerland)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|demis-roussos|goodbye-my-love-goodbye}}\n\n{{Demis Roussos}}\n\n[[Category:1973 songs]]\n[[Category:1973 singles]]\n[[Category:Demis Roussos songs]]\n[[Category:Philips Records singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Spain]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Germany]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Ultratop 50 Singles (Flanders) number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Leo Leandros]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Leo Leandros]]\n", "text_old": "{{redirect|Goodbye My Love, Goodbye|the 2006 Italian film|The Goodbye Kiss (film)}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Demis Roussos]]\n| album      = [[Forever and Ever (Demis Roussos album)|Forever and Ever]]\n| EP         =\n| written    =\n| published  = \n| released   = {{start date|1973}}\n| format     = 7\" vinyl single (45 RPM)\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n| length     =\n| label      = [[Philips Records|Philips]]\n| writer     = [[Leo Leandros]], [[Klaus Munro]]\n| composer   =\n| lyricist   =\n| producer   = [[Leo Leandros]]\n| prev_title = [[My Reason]]\n| prev_year  = 1972\n| title      =\n| next_title = [[Forever and Ever (Demis Roussos song)|Forever and Ever]]\" /<br />\"[[Velvet Mornings]]\n| next_year  = 1973\n| prev_track =\n| track_no   =\n| next_track =\n}}\n\n\"'''Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye'''\" is a song by Greek singer [[Demis Roussos]]. It was released as a [[single (music)|single]] in 1973.\n\nThe song was included on Roussos' 1973 album ''[[Forever and Ever (Demis Roussos album)|Forever and Ever]]''.\n\n== Background and writing ==\nThe song was written by [[Leo Leandros]] and [[Klaus Munro]]. The recording was produced by [[Leo Leandros]].<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" />\n\nThere is also a Spanish-language version, titled \"Adi\u00f3s, mi amor, adi\u00f3s\".<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.discogs.com/D%C3%A9mis-Roussos-Forever-And-Ever-Eternamente/release/4263690\n|title=D\u00e9mis Roussos* - Forever And Ever = Eternamente (Vinyl, LP, Album) at Discogs\n|accessdate=2017-10-26}}</ref>\n\n== Commercial performance ==\nThe song reached no. 1 in Germany, Switzerland,<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Demis+Roussos&titel=Goodbye%2C+My+Love%2C+Goodbye&cat=s\n|title=spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\n|accessdate=2017-10-23}}</ref> Belgium (Flanders),<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye (English)\">{{cite web\n|url=http://www.spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Demis+Roussos&titel=Goodbye%2C+My+Love%2C+Goodbye+%5BEnglish%5D&cat=s\n|title=spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye <nowiki>[English]</nowiki>\n|accessdate=2017-10-23}}</ref> and [[Spain]].\n\n== Track listings ==\n'''7\" single Philips 6009 318''' (1973, Germany, Ireland)<br />\n'''7\" single RTB S 53695''' (1973, Yugoslavia)\n: A. \"Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" (3:58)\n: B. \"Mara\" (3:59)<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" />\n\n'''7\" single Philips 6009 392''' (1973, Italy)\n: A. \"Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" (3:56)\n: B. \"My Friend The Wind\" (3:55)<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" /><ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye (English)\" />\n\n'''7\" single Philips 6009 364''' (1973, Netherlands)\n: A. \"Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" (3:58)\n: B. \"No Way Out\" (3:10)<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" /><ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye (English)\" />\n\n'''7\" single Philips 6009 381''' (1973, France, Portural<!--, Angola-->)\n: A. \"Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" (3:56)\n: B. \"Yellow Paper\" (3:04)<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" /><ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye (English)\" />\n\n'''7\" single Philips 60 09 400''' (1973, Spain)\n: A. \"Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye\" (3:56)\n: B. \"Lay It Down\" (3:45)<ref name=\"spanishcharts.com - Demis Roussos - Goodbye, My Love, Goodbye (English)\" />\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (1973)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|2|artist=Demis Roussos|song=Good